    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="436"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–554: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-05T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 5, 1954—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 109. Repeated information Paris 202.
                    Reference: <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 105, repeated Paris 200.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d436fn1">Dated May 5, <ref target="#pg_694">p.
                        694</ref>.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> states <persName corresp="#p_GAA1"
                        >Gromyko</persName> raised objection to present three chairmen or <persName
                        corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> alone or any outsider or to letting nine
                    choose.</p>
                <p>He proposed rotation among five or among four (leaving out France as participant
                    in fighting), both of which <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> of
                    course rejected. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> stated rotation
                    of <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> and USSR unacceptable to French.</p>
                <p>Although he might easily have done so <persName corresp="#p_GAA1"
                        >Gromyko</persName> made no mention of including India or additional
                    participants.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> dining with <persName
                        corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> tonight and they will discuss it further,
                    with <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> again pressing for either
                    rotation of three or <persName corresp="#p_WWKNB1">Wan</persName> alone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
